# Fast pre-push: lint + typecheck only.
#
# Rationale: a pre-push hook should catch the most common breakages without
# being slower or more brittle than `git push` itself. The previous hook ran
# the full vitest suite (`pnpm test`), which:
#   - Took 130–180 s per push, locking the developer's terminal
#   - Intermittently failed on time-mock tests under heavy parallel load
#     (RunScreen.coaching tier-2, framework-detection, etc.) — these flakes
#     reproduce on clean main and have nothing to do with most pushes
#
# Net effect: contributors learned to push with `--no-verify`, defeating the
# entire purpose of the hook. Worse, every flake triggered a "is my change
# actually broken?" investigation that almost always concluded "no, it was
# the timer test again."
#
# Fix: run only the checks that are fast AND reliable:
#   - lint (eslint cache, ~3–8 s)
#   - typecheck (tsc --noEmit, ~8–15 s)
#
# CI runs the full vitest suite on every PR with dedicated hardware, so unit-
# test regressions are caught at the gate before merge. The pre-push job is
# now ~15 s of signal vs. ~180 s of noise.
pnpm lint:eslint && pnpm exec tsc --noEmit
